SIMPLE: ilk
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ilk
<hw>Ilk</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Scot. <ets>ilk</ets>, OE.
<ets>ilke</ets> the same, AS. <ets>ilca</ets>. Cf. <er>Each</er>.]</ety>
<def>Same; each; every.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Of that ilk</b></col>, <sd>(a)</sd> <cd>denoting that a
person's surname and the title of his estate are the same; as,
<xex>Grant of that ilk</xex>, i.e., <xex>Grant of Grant</xex>.</cd>
<mark>[Scottish]</mark> <rj><au>Jamieson.</au></rj> <sd>(a)</sd> <cd>Of
the same kind.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ilk</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Ilk
<hw>Ilk</hw> <pr>(⟦icr⟧lk)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Kind; class; sort;
type; <as>as, him and his <ex>ilk</ex></as>; -- sometimes used to
indicate disapproval when applied to people.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ilke</ent>⟦br⟧
